                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-195-off1027 t18220911-195-victim1859"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-195-person1860">
                  JOHN 
                  HELLYER
               <interp inst="t18220911-195-person1860" type="surname" value="HELLYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-195-person1860" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-195-person1860" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18220911-195-viclabel1029" type="occupation">drive the Salisbury Van</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-195-victim1859 t18220911-195-viclabel1029"></join>. On the 2d of August, about half past four o'clock in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18220911-195-crimeloc1030">Norman's Coffee-room in Wych-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-195-crimeloc1030" type="placeName" value="Norman's Coffee-room in Wych-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-195-crimeloc1030" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-195-off1027 t18220911-195-crimeloc1030"></join>. I had left my coat on the box of the van, which stood at the door; a man alarmed me, I ran out, took the prisoner is a cellar, and found the coat just by him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-195-person1861">
                  JAMES 
                  NORMAN
               <interp inst="t18220911-195-person1861" type="surname" value="NORMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-195-person1861" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-195-person1861" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner take the coat off the box, and put it on his shoulder. I followed him into<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182209110092"></xptr>cellar, a few yards off, secured him in the passage, and found the coat in the cellar where I had seen him go.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I know nothing of it; the news of my apprehension has caused the death of my wife.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18220911-195-verdict1031" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18220911-195-verdict1031" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22.</p>
